The Waldo Theatre on Main Street in downtown Waldoboro. (Gregory Rec/Staff Photographer)

Keri Lupien wants people to know there’s a lot more to Waldoboro than what most of us see passing through the Midcoast town on Route 1.

That’s where the landmark eatery Moody’s Diner is, of course. But just a couple minutes away is Waldoboro’s quaint downtown and a scenic town landing.

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/26490267_20210923_waldo-theater_3_322692.jpg?w=250&h=250&crop=1)](https://www.pressherald.com/2021/10/03/with-its-space-restored-and-mission-renewed-waldo-theatre-is-ready-for-its-encore/)

