Lupien is the talent and live music booking agent for the **[Waldo Theatre](https://www.thewaldotheatre.org/),** which was built in 1936 and extensively renovated and re-opened in 2021. She took a few minutes to share some of her favorite things to do and places to visit in town. Some are seasonal so check websites for hours.

**Where do you like to eat?**
---

I tell everyone that a homemade biscuit with butter and jam at [**Perch**](https://www.facebook.com/p/Perch-Cafe-and-Bakery-100095674895203/) is NOT to  
be missed. I could eat one every day for breakfast. Speaking of carbs, I love eating the wood-fired pizza at **[Odd Alewives](https://oddalewives.com/)** and then walking through the gardens that provide the toppings.  
Although they’re closed during the winter, it’s also a wonderfully cozy place on a rainy day too.  

