Riverbrook Preserve in Waldoboro protects 1.5 miles of frontage on the Medomak River. (Carey Kish photo)

**Where do you go for a drink?**
---

**[Ida’s Wine Bar](https://thewaldoboroinn.com/idas-wine-bar)** at The Waldoboro Inn. Housed in the mansion’s carriage house, this is the place to go for a glass of natural wine. You’re just as likely to chat with a first-time visitor to Maine, a visual artist from NYC, a local businessperson or just enjoy the beautiful backyard gardens. In the winter, the local vibes at [**The Narrows Tavern**](https://www.facebook.com/NarrowsTavern/) provide a real sense of community, especially if you can catch a local music jam session.

